				<h3>How is supercomputer performance measured?</h3>
				<p>To perform well across a broad set interesting problems, a machine must have a balanced mix of computation, memory, and IO. The TOP500 list uses the LINPACK linear algebra benchmark created in the 1970s as a yard stick to compare performance. Another possibility is to simply look at peak performance numbers of the machines and quote things like GFLOPS and GigaBytes. A supercomputer should be measured on the ability to get the job done. The question is really “what job?”.</p>
			</div>
			<hr class='col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1'>
		</div>

