				<h3>What is the fastest supercomputer today?</h3>
				<p> Based on the Top500 list, it is the Tianhe-2, a supercomputer developed by China’s National University of Defense Technology. It provides 33.86 petaflop/s (quadrillions of calculations per second) on the Linpack benchmark and includes over 3 Million CPU cores. </p> 
			</div>
